snippet.textDisplay:
Jellybeans just shouldn’t exist. 0:50 yeah, red flag #1: if it smells terrible, don’t put it in your mouth. Beyond that, if the texture when bitten isn’t as it is when held, do not continue to hold it in your mouth. And if it doesn’t taste like what they say it tastes like, spit it out. And if artificial colors are needed, spit it out. Food should pride itself more on the flavor, not the color.
5:25 wtf do you mean “chewy texture”? They aren’t chewy. Bit them, and they demolecularize. They aren’t chewy, they dissolve like a 20-year-old pack of juicy fruit gum, which equally doesn’t deserve to exist.
